{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FSNCP1TrA6p4ETyvUK7rYj","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# integrate-platform\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\t\n5\tWire the metrics and iam components into a single binary at cmd/platform/main.go. The binary starts the metrics HTTP listener on port 8081 and the IAM HTTP listener on port 8082 in separate goroutines, then blocks until a shutdown signal. There must be exactly one main package in the entire codebase.\n6\t\n7\tEnd-to-end acceptance tests (net/http against live listeners started in TestMain or a helper) must cover all 12 endpoints verbatim from the spec:\n8\t\n9\tMetrics listener (port 8081):\n10\tPOST /events body:{\"type\":\"click-mouse\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}} → 201 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"type\":\"<string>\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}};\n11\tPOST /events body:{\"type\":\"submit-form\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}} → 201 (same shape);\n12\tGET /events → 200 JSON array containing previously posted events.\n13\t\n14\tIAM listener (port 8082):\n15\tPOST /users body:{\"username\":\"<string>\",\"password\":\"<string>\"} → 201 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"username\":\"<string>\"} (no password field);\n16\tGET /users/{id} → 200 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"username\":\"<string>\"} or 404;\n17\tDELETE /users/{id} → 200/204 on existing user or 404 on missing;\n18\tPOST /auth/login body:{\"username\":\"<string>\",\"password\":\"<string>\"} → 200 {\"token\":\"<string>\"};\n19\tPOST /auth/logout header:Authorization:Bearer <token> → 200/204;\n20\tPOST /roles body:{\"name\":\"<string>\",\"permissions\":[\"<string>\"]} → 201 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"name\":\"<string>\",\"permissions\":[\"<string>\"]};\n21\tGET /roles → 200 JSON array;\n22\tPOST /users/{id}/roles body:{\"roleId\":\"<string>\"} → 200/201;\n23\tGET /users/{id}/roles → 200 JSON array;\n24\tPOST /authz/check body:{\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"permission\":\"<string>\"} → 200 {\"allowed\":<bool>}.\n25\t\n26\t## Context\n27\t\n28\t### Level 1 — fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n29\t\n30\t\n31\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47ffb4dd-649b-4f80-9094-fd10b5b9797a","uuid":"11ebbe12-63fc-4bed-b48e-963b8021d0cf","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:26:05.655Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/target/project/tasks/main/in-progress/fbc6d9-platform/fbc6d9-0000-build-1/fbc6d9-0002-integrate-platform/README.md","content":"# integrate-platform\n\n## Goal\n\nWire the metrics and iam components into a single binary at cmd/platform/main.go. The binary starts the metrics HTTP listener on port 8081 and the IAM HTTP listener on port 8082 in separate goroutines, then blocks until a shutdown signal. There must be exactly one main package in the entire codebase.\n\nEnd-to-end acceptance tests (net/http against live listeners started in TestMain or a helper) must cover all 12 endpoints verbatim from the spec:\n\nMetrics listener (port 8081):\nPOST /events body:{\"type\":\"click-mouse\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}} → 201 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"type\":\"<string>\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}};\nPOST /events body:{\"type\":\"submit-form\",\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"payload\":{}} → 201 (same shape);\nGET /events → 200 JSON array containing previously posted events.\n\nIAM listener (port 8082):\nPOST /users body:{\"username\":\"<string>\",\"password\":\"<string>\"} → 201 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"username\":\"<string>\"} (no password field);\nGET /users/{id} → 200 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"username\":\"<string>\"} or 404;\nDELETE /users/{id} → 200/204 on existing user or 404 on missing;\nPOST /auth/login body:{\"username\":\"<string>\",\"password\":\"<string>\"} → 200 {\"token\":\"<string>\"};\nPOST /auth/logout header:Authorization:Bearer <token> → 200/204;\nPOST /roles body:{\"name\":\"<string>\",\"permissions\":[\"<string>\"]} → 201 {\"id\":\"<string>\",\"name\":\"<string>\",\"permissions\":[\"<string>\"]};\nGET /roles → 200 JSON array;\nPOST /users/{id}/roles body:{\"roleId\":\"<string>\"} → 200/201;\nGET /users/{id}/roles → 200 JSON array;\nPOST /authz/check body:{\"userId\":\"<string>\",\"permission\":\"<string>\"} → 200 {\"allowed\":<bool>}.\n\n## Context\n\n### Level 1 — fbc6d9-0000-build-1\n\n\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
